column2: Q) can i use a share acct for the bank and an individual acct for CDP? what is the min and max investment? how much she have when for example, the interest is 2%,invest $1k,hold for 6mth?A) yes, can use share atm acct, only CDP acct have to be individual. min of $500,max of $50k. the interest rate will be 1% since she gg to hold for 6mth. she will have the total amt of $1010.

Q:Are the new interest rates out already? So the maximum investment is $100K? Can i apply now?A: The interest rates are published on the website at 430pm.The maximum investment is $50K first month and $100K at any one time.But 50K investment does not guarantee $50K bonds issued.If you are issued for $20K, $30K refundment.    Application officially opens on 1st Sept 6pm.
HOW TO OPEN CDP A/C? ADVISED HER TO LOGIN TO WEBSITE AND PRINT OUT THE CDP APPLICATION AND MAIL IT. NEED TO WAIT FOR CDP REPLY APPROX. 10 DAYS TO 2 WEEKS.

Caller using UOB but not aware of interest rate ,advised her taht interest rates will be published after 6pm,today.Advised her if ssb website also,allotment and application process.Daily application time freom Mon-Sat,7am-9pm,not available on public holiday.

Question: caller want to know how apply for the savings bondsasn: first you need to have a cdp account with you than follow by dcs activation done than go to the atm machine to apply for the savings bonds

Called in to check if she could use ATM card without her name on it to purchase the bond with her own individual CDP account - answered her yes.Also check if she has DCS activated but she was unsure, thus i gave her CDP number to called in.

Time: 13:16 PMEnquiry: Resolved caller's enquiry on the need of CDP Acc,min/max bond holding,interest rate guaranteed.Clarified with that caller on CDP Acc is needed w DCS activation ,min/ max holding for per bond and overall.The interest rate in the event (for example) of drastic change in the market/interest will be adjusted to a near interest that is promised,not fully at such events but the approx interest adjustment will close to the interest promised.
Caller asked if her bank account is POSB but her CDP account is UOB,,is it alright ?Informed her that its alright as it is the designated bank account is for tranference of interest payout.
Caller said she has an existing CDP account but is unaware whether it is DCS activated. Gave her the CDP hotline.

Q: What are the interest rates for the new coming bonds. Which banks are participating? Whats the minimum investment? A: Interest rates will be published on the website at 430pm. DBS,POSB,OCBC & UOB are participating banks only DBS/POSB has ibanking. The minimum investment is $500 with $2 bank application charge\

Q) when is the last day to apply? when will it open the next month?A) on the 25th sept at 9 pm. next application will be on the 1st business day of the month and it will be close on the 4th business day before month-end.

Question : how to apply for the savings bonds asn: for the savings bonds right firstly u need to have a cdp account with u .. secondly u can apply for the savings bonds today at 6pm onwards at the atm machine..

Time:14:00PMEnquiry: Resolved caller's enquiry on the interest rate.Clarified that the exact interest will be published at 6pm at ssbond's website,its a step-up interest,the interest rate published as an example is a rough guide.

Dear Sir/Madam I am Chidambaram Pichappan (NRIC: S7374341I).  I am Singaporean currently residing in Qatar. I have DBS Bank account and CDP account as well.  Am I eligible to apply for bond ? thanksPichappan------------------------  replied at 1.07pm -----------------------------Dear Pichappan, Thank you for your interest in Savings Bonds. You may use your DBS internet banking to apply for the bonds. May i just ask, do you have the token given by the DBS bank? Also for your CDP account, have your DCS been activated? If yes, you may apply for the Savings Bonds from today, 6pm onwards. We hope that the above information is of assistance to you. For more information on the Singapore Savings Bond, you may wish to visit our website at : http://www.sgs.gov.sg/savingsbonds.aspxIf you have any further queries, please feel free to contact us at our hotline at +656221-3682 (Mon-Fri, 8.30am to 5.30pm, excluding Public Holidays) or email us at : contact@savingsbonds.sg Thank you for your time and consideration. We wish you a pleasant day ahead. Best Regards, Mayvelle KwokCustomer Service OfficerSingapore Savings Bond Customer Service Centre
Caller wanted to know how to open a CDP account. Advised accordingly.

Q) can i use a joint account to apply for SSB? after getting my CDP account, can i apply  for SSB ibanking for DBS?A) yes possible, as long it is an individual account. yes u can apply for SSB after u get ur CDP account ready. Max amount is $50k, overall can hold up to $100k.

Please let me know whether I can use the fund from my SRS account to subscribe to the Singapore Savings Bonds.ThanksEdward Wong--- replied ---Dear Edward, Thank you for your interest in Savings Bonds. SRS is not applicable to purchase for the Savings Bonds. To apply for Savings Bonds, you need to have a DBS/POSB, OCBC or UOB bank account and ATM card. This is because applications will be through the ATMs and there will be a transaction fee of $2 per application. For more information on the Singapore Savings Bonds, you may wish to visit our website at : http://www.sgs.gov.sg/savingsbonds.aspx  We hope that the above information is of assistance to you. If you have any further queries, please feel free to contact us at our hotline at 6221-3682 (Mon-Fri, 8.30am to 5.30pm, excluding Public Holidays) or email us at : contact@savingsbonds.sg Thank you for your time and consideration. We wish you a pleasant day ahead. Best Regards,Mayvelle KwokCustomer Service OfficerSingapore Savings Bonds Customer Service Centre

Caller was told by Maybank that he needs to sign up for a Securities broker a/c with SGX so that he can sign for a CDP a/c to purchase SSB.Resolution: Called CDP to clarify. CDP not available. Clarified with other agents before adv. caller about going to Maybank.

I have sent in my application a month ago to apply for a CDP Securities Account in order to purchase the SSB. My NRIC is S8524097/H (Khoo Li Jing Wendy), can you please check and advise if I'm eligible to purchase the bond for the month of November?----replied----Dear Wendy,Thank you for your enquiries about the Singapore Savings Bonds.You may wish to email CDP at asksgx@sgx.com or call their hotline at 65357511 for more details on your application form. Alternatively, you may wish to wait for the CDP letter to be sent to your house. Once CDP application is successful, you will receive a 12 digit CDP code which will be needed when applying for Singapore Savings Bonds.We hope that the above information is of assistance to you. For more information on the Singapore Savings Bonds, you may wish to visit our website at : http://www.sgs.gov.sg/savingsbonds.aspx .If you have any further queries, please feel free to contact us at our hotline at 6221-3682 (Mon-Fri, 8.30am to 5.30pm, excluding Public Holidays) or email us at : contact@savingsbonds.sg .We appreciate your interest in Singapore Savings Bonds. To help us improve on our service, we would appreciate if you could complete a short survey at this website: "http://pbx.rmagroup.com.sg/SSBsurvey.aspx?id=SSB002511.Thank you for your time and consideration. We wish you a pleasant day ahead.Best Regards,Mayvelle KwokCustomer Service OfficerSingapore Savings Bonds Customer Service Centre

Enquiry: Interest rate/ period  Resolution: Adv caller the interest rate from yr1-10 and the interest is calculated by yearly

Caller asked if he was successful in buying the SSB for last month as he has not received any notifications from CDP. Adviced him accordingly.

enquiry: Redemption process, fee and min amount  Resolution: Adv caller the whole  redemption process, fee, period and in multiple of 500. The month applicant submit application is calculated in for interest as the redemption proceed will only be returned the following month.
Called in to ask how much interest rate will she earn, how will she know the results of her bond - adv accordingly.
Called in to ask how much interest rate will he earn, and what is the interest rate of the previous months - adv accorrdingly.
Q: How to redeem? Is it the same way as application? How much is the charge?A:ATM,yes and $2

enquiry: request for another notification letter from cdp/ to check his bond resolution: Adv caller to check any refund after allotment day,his cdp acc and notification letter. He is not sure whether he received the notification letter from cdp and wants to request for it.There was deductionupon application.I have transferred call to cdp but call was dropped halfway. He has the hotline.
Q: Irregardless of how many times of applications i do the cap is up to $50k a month?A:Yes and 100K at any one time.Every application is $2 per charge.
Q) where can i check if i got it or nt?A) check by ur CDP,
Caller opted for redemption on 8 and 22 Oct, but $ has not be credited back to bank a/c.Resolution: Gave CDP no as CDP officers were fully engaged.

Caller requested to know SSB interest rates. Adv. on scheduled interest rates.

Called in to clarify the public notice.
